reviewText: I had never seen this movie before and thought it would be along the lines of what I have seen Like Jason movies but was not what I expected it was kind of boring
Poor quality, difficult to see faces
The cinematography was too old.  Couldn't hardly see the characters.  I only watched the first 10-15 minutes.  Didn't enjoy it.
I did not think was as old a movie as it was. I might watch it when I am in the mood for that kind of movie.
I was bored and decided to view this movie from the past. I was surprised. It kept my attention and good story line.
Too cheesey,only watched first 10 min. The picture Quality was poor.
the plot and special effects are good for the time of production but the quality of the DVD itself was poor ; a bit faded and grainy perhaps there is a digitally enhanced version?
These are my kind of movies.

I tried to watch it.  Couldn't do it though.  First, it was on the same level as a spaghetti western type movie. It was all Italian long before Italian directors had a clue.  I may have considered two stars just for the heck of it......but.....naw.  Twenty years ago I may have given it two stars, but not today.
Take from that what you will.
About as poor of a copy of this movie you will never watch. Perhaps it's a cult classic? I don't know, I didn't even make 5 minutes in.
There were no giants and the acting was terrible.

The story of Jason and the Argonauts how could you not appreciate it. granted it had a  lot to be desired, used the same plot line as most of these Italian films, but it was an absolute pleasure to watch the myth come to life. They were missing some of the more Heroic Argonauts like Hercules and such, but the story was decent and the effects, although nothing really fancy managed to  fit the movie and of course the bad guys die at the end.
Not even on the level of The Seventh Voyage of Sinbad or Jason And The Argonauts. Terrible movie.
